TRANSLATE INPUT OVERVIEW

@include.the.translate.command

  FROM MICROPHONE - DEFAULT DEVICE or SPECIFIC DEVICE

    The `spx translate` command can translate streaming audio captured
    from a device microphone (default microphone or specific microphone).

    To translate audio from a device MICROPHONE see: spx help translate microphone 

  FROM FILE - SINGLE or MULTIPLE FILES

    The `spx translate` command can also translate audio stored in local
    or remote audio files, in various audio container formats (e.g. mp3, ogg).

    To translate from a single audio FILE see: spx help translate file
    To translate from a multiple audio FILES see: spx help translate files
    To translate from file(s) in various FORMATs see: spx help translate format
 
EXAMPLES

  `EXAMPLE 1`: Translate speech from microphone
  
    spx translate --microphone --source en-US --target de

  `EXAMPLE 2`: Translate from local WAV file, or remote MP3 file

    spx translate --file hello.wav --source en-US --target de
    spx translate --file http://crbn.us/hello.mp3 --format mp3 --source en-US --target de

  `EXAMPLE 3`: Translate multiple files using wildcards

    spx translate --files *.wav --source en-US --target de

